The Twelvefold Way:

$|\{f:k \to n \}|$

How many ways to sort $k$ balls into $n$ boxes?

\begin{tabular}{|l | c | c | c| }
 \hline
 \hline
 &
 \makecell{Arbitrary\\\small{any sorting}}
 &
 \makecell{Injective\\\small{max 1 ball per box}}
 &
 \makecell{Surjective\\\small{each box gets ball}}
 \\
\hline
\makecell{Distinct Balls\\
Distinct Boxes} & $n^k$ & $\frac{n!}{(n-k)!}$ & $n! \stirling k n$ \\
\hline
\makecell{
Identical Balls\\
Distinct Boxes} & $\binom{n+k-1}{k}$ & $\binom{n}{k}$ & $\binom{k-1}{n-1}$ \\
\hline
\makecell{Distinct Balls\\
Identical Boxes} & $\sum_{j=0}^n \stirling k j$ & 1 if $k\leq n$ & $\stirling k n$\\
\hline
\makecell{Identical Balls\\
Identical Boxes} & $p_{\leq n}(k)$ & 1 if $k\leq n$ & $p_n(k)$\\
\hline
\hline
\end{tabular}

text.tspan: Integer Partitions with at most k parts
How many football games are there?
